<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1817-04-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1817-04-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="68" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                            <head>[64]<hi rend="italic">*Mr. <persName type="from">McCulloch</persName>, collector, to Mr. <persName type="to">Zamorano</persName> Spanish consul.</hi></head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Custom-House,
                                        Baltimore</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Collector’s
                                        Office</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1817-04-14"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 14,
                                1817</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: If you can name the vessel and specify
                                any circumstance to warrant the proceeding, immediate attention will
                                be paid to the object by pursuing her course as far as possible.</p>
                            <p>Allow me to say that if your note just received respects the ship
                                Idas, she was searched by me in consequence of certain suspicions on
                                Saturday evening, and was found without arms, ammunition, or any
                                warlike equipment, and cleared in ballast coastwise.</p>
                            <p>I am, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <list>
                                        <item>J. H. McCULLOCH.</item>
                                        <item>Don <hi rend="smallcaps">Joaquin
                                                Zamorano</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Consul of
                                                Spain.</hi></item>
                                    </list>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>